description:
The Red Onslaught is broadcasting waves of telepathic hate across the globe -- and Marvel's greatest heroes have turned on their moral axis! What will the Avengers and X-Men find in the Red Skull's bleak "re-education camps"? What is Tony Stark's dark secret? And with the heroes "inverted" to evil, who will stand against them? How about an army of villains?! Magneto betrays his alliance, a founding Avenger quits, and the Scarlet Witch is forced to join Dr. Doom! And who are Kluh and the Sorceress Supreme? As the Axis of Evil strikes down the heroes, the all-new Astonishing Avengers battle the Uncanny X-Men! Witness an X-Man's horrifying fate -- and an Avenger's appalling choice! Who will live or die? Who will remain inverted? The shocking climax will crack the Marvel Universe to its core!

Collects Avengers & X-Men: Axis #1-9.
name: HC

description: Alain and Shar, a struggling couple in the Los Feliz area of East Los Angeles, will have their resolve tested as a merciless heatwave threatens the sanity of everyone around them.
name: Volume 1

description: After seeing him again at a party, Athena's heart stops. Nikos! The man she said goodbye to...the man she loved. After leaving Argyros, a kingdom on a beautiful island in the middle of the Mediterranean, Athena worked hard to build up her career in New York. However, with the death of the king, as the next in line she is now being pursued by Nikos to take the throne. "I understand that he wants to help save the kingdom, but I'm just not cut out to rule over a nation." On top of holding deep secrets that she dare not tell anyone, seeing him again after ten years makes her heart ache all the more.
name: Marrying His Majesty 2

volume.name: Betrothed: To the People' s Prince

description:
Limited Edition

A collection of all Big Zeke's adventures including his origin, his battle with Tunguska and his death.

Stories by Ron Marz & Allen Cordrey with art by Cory Hamscher, Darryl Banks, Matthew Waite, Terry Austin and many more

The Dark Tower saga begins again -- on Earth! If you thought the badlands of Mid-World were dangerous, wait until you experience Brooklyn in the 1960s! Meet Eddie Dean, a troubled young man able to open doors to other worlds. Now, Eddie must survive family tragedy, haunting addiction and deadly forces that conspire to stop him from growing up to challenge the Man in Black! Without his mother, what will happen to Eddie and his brother, Henry? What horrors await within the Dutch Hill Mansion? And what offer does the criminal called Balazar make? With magic doors appearing, strange voices in his head and monstrous lobstrosities hungry for his flesh, can Eddie survive his desperate mission? Stephen King's dark fantasy epic spills onto the streets of New York City!

Collects Dark Tower: The Drawing of the Three - The Prisoner #1-5.
name: TPB

volume.name: Dark Tower: The Drawing Of The Three - The Prisoner

description:
Wolverine is dead! And with Logan out of the picture, various factions are scrambling to fill the void! Will Wolverine's decades-long legacy be shaped by the heroes who valiantly fought alongside him -- or by the villains who have challenged him during the many years of his long life? Or both? X-23 and Daken react in surprising ways to the death of the man who literally gave them life! With Logan gone, Sabretooth's rage takes on an entirely new shape and mission. Lady Deathstrike begins a quest to obtain something deadly that formerly belonged to Wolverine, while Mystique comes to grips with her lifetime of crime -- and with her destiny. And a vampiric menace shadows all of them! What monumental decision will these heroes and villains make that will forever alter Logan's legacy?

Collects Death of Wolverine: The Logan Legacy #1-7.
name: TPB

volume.name: Death of Wolverine: The Logan Legacy

description:
Collecting the celebrated four issue miniseries created by: acclaimed author Deepak Chopra.

Chopra's supernatural thriller about a businessman, Michael Morton who arrives in India with his wife, Anna and son, Ty on a vacation. While Michael is distracted on a phone call with an overseas colleague, Anna and Ty wander through a typically teeming Indian shopping bazaar. Then the inexplicable happens -- Ty watches as his mother wanders into a small store but never comes out. She's vanished without a trace. Michael searches for his wife, at first irritated by: her elusiveness, but soon turns frantic, as he can't uncover any clue to her whereabouts. Things then turn even stranger and desperate when Michael hears his wife's whispering, crying for his help. Tracking the sounds, Michael and Ty are led on adventure of both physical and metaphysical danger as they stop at nothing to reunite their family.
name: TPB

description: This edition of Deidre Dark's Delightful Dolls is a special variant cover edition that fans can only download and purchase through Iverse. This variant cover will not be available at the Comic Book Divas Publishing store; so be sure to get this variant. The Devil is always in the Details. What a talent, to be able to see the real person slinking around inside the human shell. Best not let Deidre be the dealer of your cards at the next game. When she sees the unpleasantness that is within, that is when the delicious fun begins. Deidre Dark's Delightful Dolls, a tale of those that can see, hear and smell a rat. Some of us say that revenge is a dish best served cold, but with Deidre, you might say it is one just served best. Looks can be deceiving and that goes both ways. Remember, never judge a book by its cover -some of us already know what is inside and the rest of us will just have to wait and see.

Dylan McVillain's School of Villainy #1

The city of pickleton just got a little more dangerous. Resident super villain, Dylan McVillain has opened "Dylan McVillain's School of Villainy" and he's just enrolled his first student. Will Dylan's new apprentice make him proud, or will he knock dylan off of his villainous throne?

Ellen's Adventures at The Shadowland debuted in 2012 in upstate New York's Shawangunk Journal Newspaper (formerly The Ellenville Journal.)

Creator R. Robert Pollak draws the weekly seasonal comic strip in a style reminiscent of the classic newspaper comic strips of yesteryear.

The main character, Ellen Allen, is an actress at the local Shadowland Theatre in Ellenville, NY. Ellen's charm is always finding herself in precarious situations with a group of over-the-top characters, from aliens, gnomes and ghosts, to old movie stars. All of the storylines and settings are inspired by the rich history and picturesque locations in the Hudson Valley area. Some of the tongue-in-cheek cast of characters include, Gloria Swansong, Dolores del Mio and her pal, Hal. Over the years, the quirky comic strip has developed a cult following online with fans all over the globe.
name: Book 1: The Phantom of Sam's Point

description:
This issue's theme is Hope.

Loss Of Hope: Clare has always tried to fit it, but has always been alone. When her family has a chance to escape the Earth and hide on a space station, she follows them, but wonders if her dream of a true connection is finally over. What do you do when all hope is finally lost?

Brush Of Hope: Jean finally got her first artistic assignment, a vast mural for the city. She won't let the end of the world make her give up on her dream, and the more she paints, the more she finds herself influencing a city on the edge of despair.

Finite is a new Science Fiction/Fantasy 3D Digital Comic Book series.

In this issue, the Cyber Soldier and SP-22 confront their first enemy, in the form of a water/ice/wind based Elemental - or is she...? It will be quite a battle: Technology vs Nature.

A mysterious Fortress may hold the key to the origin of this powerful female Elemental.

The Girl in Dior is Clara, a freshly hired chronicler, fan of fashion and our guide in the busy corridors of the brand new house of Christian Dior. It's February 12, 1947 and the crème de la crème of Paris Haute Couture is flocking to the momentous event of Dior's first show. In a flurry of corolla shaped skirts, the parade of models file down the runway. The audience is mesmerized: it's a triumph! Carmel Snow of Harper's Bazaar cries out: "It's quite a revolution, your dresses have such a new look!" Dior's career is launched and Clara's story begins. Soon, she is picked by Dior himself to be his model...

A biography docudrama marrying fiction and the story of one of the greatest couturier in history, it is also a breathless and stunning presentation of his best designs such as Audrey Hepburn or Lauren Bacall wore, rendered by bestselling artist Annie Goetzinger, seen for the first time on this side of the Atlantic.
name: GN

description:
Hooray for Hollywood

Kidnapped from the planet Earth to the Planet Sq'id, Holly Wood must struggle with the leadership of the peace keeping S'p'r forces and her desire for wealth and lavish comfort.
name: Hooray for Hollywood

description: A team of priests discovers that sin is a slope as they battle to save their parish by any means necessary. A graphic novel in the style of Breaking Bad.
name: Vol. 1

description: "Like A Virus" is a one-shot 23-page comic book about one supernaturally gifted person investigating -- and confronting -- a longtime haunting in her neighborhood. It's also about the guilt and fear that can anchor a soul down, and how those thoughts can spread and contaminate not just you, but the people around you.
Machiavelli is a historically accurate graphic novel; hand drawn, hand painted and set in Renaissance Florence.
name: GN

description: 'Machine Translations' is the fictionalized autobiography and comic book début of Melbourne author and musician Matthew Stoff, recalling his experience growing up as an autistic child in regional Australia. It describes his unique way of understanding himself and his place in the world, with distinct, nostalgic artwork influenced by early computer games.

volume.name: Machine Translations: A Robot's Path to Self-Expression and Learning to Live With Organics

description: Detective Edward Knight has had enough. In the face of crippling corruption, he makes a choice that will forever alter his life.

"Penny Dreadful's Cauldron Of Terror" contains two haunting stories that will take you back to the days of the classic EC Comics (For those Dreary Ones and comic book fans that are too young to remember EC Comics, please check them out at your favorite comic book store). Penny has created and written two stories that will give both "Dreary Ones" and comic book fans a good chill and chuckle with her creations "Sprite Fright" and "Puppy Love". The first story entitled "Sprite Fright", Penny takes you to a storybook time, and tells the tale of a little girl named "Christina" and her sprite friend "Cymbeline"; she and "Cymbeline"; along with the other sprite and fairy friends talk and play games in the garden, but when the sunsets "Christina" must say goodbye to "Cymbeline" and her other magical friends until the next day. "Christina" wants to invite her friends inside the house to play after sunset but Christina's mother will not allow her to invite them into the house. What happens when Christina's mother leaves her alone with her baby sister and invites her friends into the house? Penny Dreadful's next story comes straight from the question, "How did Penny And Garou Meet?" in a story entitled "Puppy Love", since Penny wants to keep this story a surprise for her fans.

No Stone Unturned

What happens when an average Joe or a petty criminal becomes a god or a demon? For, whom so ever finds an ancient gemstone in Dave Ryan's Penance - shall be endowed with unlimited mystical power.

In primordial times, twenty-four magical gemstones were scattered throughout the world in an attempt to find worthy bearers of their eldritch power. Each gem is a conduit of the local mythos in which it hides and is a gateway to the realm of the supernatural world.

Both good and evil men have uncovered the gemstones and are in a race for omnipotence over all mankind. With limitless power, and no idea how to use it, will the heroes and villains of Penance open up the very gates of Heaven and Hell?
name: No Stone Unturned

description: It is a collection of short stories about young girl Poppy, by Matjaz and Jelena Bertoncelj, about the beauty and kindness in the children's world.
name: GN

description:
Dead means Dead

Psypher was a superhero who died five years ago at the hands of the Living Nightmare. Now, somebody else has taken up the mantle...
name: Dead Means Dead

description:
Bunty was a British comic magazine aimed at girls which appeared weekly from 1958 to 2001. Each issue was a mixture of short one-off strips and ongoing serials alongside features and activities designed for young girls. School stories, horses, ballet, and tales of overcoming adversity were popular Bunty staples.

Among the regular series, the title character, Bunty - described as 'A Girl Like You' - appeared in her own humorous single page comic strip, Moira Kent featured the trials and triumphs of an aspiring ballerina, and The Four Marys featured a gang of loyal friends at a girls' boarding school.

These regular strips, and many more, also appeared in The Bunty Annual, the hardback compilation of strips, stories and features which ran from 1960 until 2009. This 'Best of' compilation brings together a selection of classic Bunty Annual strips and features from across the years.

volume.name: Retro Classics: The Best of Bunty Annual

description:
In 1956, long-running British humour comics The Dandy, The Beano, and their most recent sister paper, The Topper, were joined by The Beezer, bringing a mix of comedy strips and adventure stories for kids on a weekly basis until 1990 when it merged with the Topper into The Beezer & Topper for the final few years of its existence.

An annual Beezer Book appeared alongside the weekly comic from 1957 onwards, and even outlasted the comic, the last Beezer Book appearing in 2002, nearly a decade after The Beezer & Topper ceased publication. This Best of The Beezer Annual collection revisits some of the favourite strips and stars from those well-loved books, with appearances from future Beano stars The Numskulls (and a solo strip from Beano legend Plug), plus Colonel Blink, Ginger, The Banana Bunch, and lots more!

volume.name: Retro Classics: The Best of The Beezer Annual

description:
From 1933 to 1981 The Hotspur brought tales of pluck, courage and derring-do to its audience every week. Beginning as a story paper, in 1959 it transformed from mainly text-based tales into a dynamic comic magazine. For the next few decades The Hotspur thrilled its readers with a mix of war stories, espionage escapades, wild west adventure and action-packed superheroics!

As well as the weekly comic, The Hotspur Annual brought an extra dose of drama every Christmas. These hardback books featured extended adventures for the stars of the comic, alongside one-off stories and special features designed to appeal to the mainly male audience. The Hotspur Annual actually outlived its weekly counterpart by a full decade.

This 'Best of' compilation is just a small sampling of strips and features from the annuals over the years, with appearances from legendary Hotspur stars The Wolf of Kabul (British Intelligence agent on the Northwest Frontier and his cricket bat-wielding companion, Chung), King Cobra (superhero alter-ego of journalist Bill King as he wages war on the crimes he reports), The Black Sapper (former high-tech master-criminal turned champion of justice) and many more.

volume.name: Retro Classics: The Best of The Hotspur Annual

description:
The Topper was a weekly British humour comic for kids that launched in 1953 and ran until 1990, when it was meged with companion comic The Beezer. Created as a stablemate to the famous comics The Dandy and The Beano, it featured a similar mix of funny strips and adventure stories, and artwork from now-legendary artists like Dudley D. Watkins (original artist on The Dandy's Desperate Dan) on Mickey the Monkey, and David Law (original artist on The Beano's Dennis the Menace) drawing Beryl the Peril.

The Best of the Topper Annual collects some of the funniest strips from The Topper Book, which appeared annually as a Christmas treat from 1954 to 1994. Join Mickey the Monkey, Beryl the Peril, Nick Kelly, Julius Cheeser and many more comic pals for fun from across four decades of The Topper.

volume.name: Retro Classics: The Best of The Topper Annual

description: The cult favorite series from Bluewater together at last. Follow the high stakes adventures of rambunctious, wise-cracking grandparents Ruth and Freddy as they strive to understand why they've been brought back as zombies from the afterlife to save those they love from a global plague that threatens to engulf humanity when a cruel game of the Gods opens the gates of the underworld and the dead are unleashed upon the living to wreak havoc!
name: TPB

description:
Abandoned Cargo

Deep in the outer rim, a ragtag crew of salvagers come across an abandoned warship... they'll need to work together or it could be their last job.
name: Abandoned Cargo

description: "Starburn" is the fastest ship in the Galaxy, its the kind of ship you don't buy you steal! That's exactly what its current owners did. The Motley Crew of space scoundrels and smugglers will take on any job for the right price.

ALL NEW HEAVENS

Two friends tell stories by the endless roaring sea.
name: All New Heavens

description: Amid a swirl of rose petals, the desert sultan solemnly materializes. Nicolette is stunned. With his well-defined face and glittering ethnic garb, he is the most fascinating thing she's ever laid eyes on! "Welcome to the land of a thousand dreams, Princess Chantal." The name he calls her in his sweet, low voice brings Nicolette back to reality. That's right, I'm here posing as my sister, Chantal, his fiancee, to trick him into making our plan work out! Ooh, but can I really take advantage of a man like him?
name: Princess Brides I

description: A paranormal investigator with supernatural abilities, Tara Normal is the real deal. Using advanced scientific technology that she invented, Tara proved to the world that ghosts exist. Now she must solve the mysterious murder of her famous mother who died while researching a book on demonology.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Cargo

Calliope travels the Cloud Ocean, but she has gotten stuck on a floating island. Now she has both a way out and a chance to help find something wondrous. If all goes to plan...
name: Cargo

description: If you searched the whole world, you'd never find a bride as happy as I am! Ashley couldn't have been more ecstatic. She gave her long-guarded purity to Devon, a man any woman would love to be with, and the next day, he surprised her with a romantic proposal. I want children right away! I want to turn this perfect joy into a family! But while they are on their tropical honeymoon, her dreams are shattered by a cruel truth. Devon only married her as part of a business deal with her father-he never loved her.
name: Pregnancy & Passion III

description:
From the darkened depths rises a peril greater than any Thor has ever before faced. Mangog threatens to unsheathe the Odinsword and bring Ragnarok upon the Norse gods in this collection of Asgardian classics! Plus, a cosmic battle between Galactus and Ego the Living Planet; the return of "Him," the man who would come to be known as Adam Warlock; and the universe-shaking origin of Galactus! Thor's adventures get personal, too, with a surprising revelation regarding Donald Blake, the return of Jane Foster, and the dramatic dance between Balder and the Norn queen Karnilla!

Collecting Thor (1966) #154-174.
name: TPB

volume.name: Thor Epic Collection: To Wake The Mangog

description:
2015 is set to be the strongest yet for Titan Comics and our readers! There's a whole new slate of outstanding NEW and CLASSIC titles coming soon from the world's gratest comics talent! In this preview, you can feast your eyes on breaking news and never-before seen previews of some top-flight comics and graphic novels being released in early 2015 and beyond.

Don't miss your chance to discover the break-out characters and top creators of tomorrow.

Suspended-cop John Dakota just wanted a nice day out at the zoo with his kid. Unfortunately, an international diamond smuggler, a group of violent mercenaries, and a swath of wild animals are about to collide and Dakota is caught in the middle.

If you love the violence and mayhem of 80s and 90s action films, you need to read UNCAGED. It'll wrap you in a warm blanket of blood, bullets, and death.

LarryBoy and the Reckless Ruckus

VeggieTales SuperComics brings all the zaniest and fun you've come to expect in a popular new format. This comic includes the story, LarryBoy and the Reckless Ruckus.

volume.name: VeggieTales SuperComics: LarryBoy and the Reckless Ruckus
